<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Third-party licenses — teemlab</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
               max-width: 56rem; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; line-height: 1.55;
               color: #1b1b1f; background: #fff; }
        h1 { border-bottom: 2px solid #ff8c33; padding-bottom: .3rem; }
        h2 { margin-top: 2.2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: .2rem; }
        .intro { color: #444; }
        ul.crates { columns: 2; font-size: .9rem; }
        pre { background: #f6f6f7; padding: 1rem; overflow-x: auto; border-radius: 6px;
              font-size: .82rem; white-space: pre-wrap; }
        .overview li { margin: .15rem 0; }
        a { color: #b9540f; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Third-party licenses</h1>
    <p class="intro">
        teemlab is distributed under <strong>MIT OR Apache-2.0</strong>. Its release
        binaries statically link the Rust crates listed below; this file reproduces
        their license notices, as those licenses require. The bundled fonts ship their
        own license files alongside the font data in <code>assets/fonts/</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <ul class="overview">
        {{#each overview}}
        <li><a href="#{{id}}">{{name}}</a> — {{count}} crate(s)</li>
        {{/each}}
    </ul>

    {{#each licenses}}
    <h2 id="{{id}}">{{name}}</h2>
    <h3>Used by</h3>
    <ul class="crates">
        {{#each used_by}}
        <li>
            {{#if crate.repository}}<a href="{{crate.repository}}">{{crate.name}} {{crate.version}}</a>
            {{else}}{{crate.name}} {{crate.version}}{{/if}}
        </li>
        {{/each}}
    </ul>
    <pre>{{text}}</pre>
    {{/each}}
</body>
</html>
